organic_results.title: Political dimensions of college impact on civil-libertarianism and the integration of political perspective: A longitudinal analysis
organic_results.snippet: Using longitudinal data, the extent of increased civil-libertarianism among a panel of Berkeley undergraduates is assessed, along with the central position of such attitudes in the progressive integration of students' political viewpoints in a more liberal and involved direction over two years. Examination of limited data on student dropouts and evidence from other studies provide a tentative basis for inferring that these changes probably reflected the impact of college attendance.
